main event: Civilian witnesses reported seeing five unidentified objects tracked by ground radar and visually observed from the air in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania in July 1955.
interesting points: The objects were tracked by ground radar and visually observed from the air.
The source's descriptions of the objects could possibly be attributed to meteorological activity.
The report was inconclusive and listed multiple possible explanations, including aircraft, astronomical, or insufficient data for evaluation.
The sighting occurred on July 13, 1955 at 0310Z.
The report does not include any photographs.
